18:06.633 --> 18:08.544
What?

18:08.594 --> 18:10.675
Hello, Richard.

18:12.436 --> 18:13.676
Mmm.

18:15.517 --> 18:17.118
Well,

18:18.118 --> 18:20.870
Richard Chapman
singing at music halls.

18:20.920 --> 18:23.432
I never would've believed it.

18:23.482 --> 18:26.873
I have to make a living, Mae.
Anyway, I enjoy it.

18:26.923 --> 18:29.715
And you know me.
As long as I'm singing I'm happy.

18:29.765 --> 18:32.596
I'm glad you said that,
because I have a job for you.

18:32.646 --> 18:36.077
Some new favourites with
a bit of classical thrown in.

18:36.127 --> 18:38.438
It's for a charity
concert at Selfridges.

18:38.489 --> 18:40.680
Please say you'll do it?

18:40.730 --> 18:42.731
For you I will.

18:43.811 --> 18:49.244
♪ I'll be dreaming, dear, of you

18:49.294 --> 18:53.806
♪ Day by day...

18:53.856 --> 18:55.847
All right, stop it.

18:55.897 --> 19:01.650
♪ Dreaming when the skies are blue

19:01.700 --> 19:07.853
♪ When they're grey... ♪

19:07.903 --> 19:10.625
Oh, you haven't changed a bit.

19:12.025 --> 19:14.417
You'll have to smarten me up
a little.

19:14.467 --> 19:16.737
My dress code has seen better days.

19:16.788 --> 19:20.460
Oh, I can arrange that.
I bet you can arrange anything now.

19:20.509 --> 19:22.980
You landed your stage-door johnny.

19:23.030 --> 19:26.112
It's what all the girls wanted
but you got it.

19:28.354 --> 19:29.834
I did.

19:32.075 --> 19:35.877
I'm beginning to think that... maybe
it was a mistake.

19:38.278 --> 19:40.229
He does love you.

19:40.279 --> 19:44.031
I... I don't think
Loxley knows what love is.

19:44.081 --> 19:46.082
Then why did he marry you?

19:47.522 --> 19:48.833
Well,

19:48.883 --> 19:51.794
everyone wanted me that season,
do you remember?

19:51.844 --> 19:53.846
For some reason
I was the "in" thing.

19:55.166 --> 19:57.767
Loxley likes to get
what other people want.

19:59.769 --> 20:02.200
I'm to blame as well, though.

20:02.250 --> 20:04.731
I married him for money
and for his power.

20:06.772 --> 20:09.013
I thought I could keep him at bay,
you see?

20:10.934 --> 20:12.935
I was wrong.

20:14.776 --> 20:16.967
Leave him. He doesn't own you.

20:17.017 --> 20:22.489
He owns everything I stand up in.
Who cares about fur coats? I do.

20:22.540 --> 20:26.931
What's so great about this thing
anyway? Well, it keeps me warm.

20:26.982 --> 20:28.983
A good man would do that.

20:33.225 --> 20:35.696
You're a clever girl, Mae.

20:35.746 --> 20:39.708
You have a big heart.
You deserve to be happy.

20:48.793 --> 20:50.794
Coming here and seeing you,

20:53.475 --> 20:56.157
it's reminded me of
a girl that I used to be.

20:59.478 --> 21:01.479
She wasn't so bad, was she?

21:05.401 --> 21:07.402
No, maybe she wasn't.

21:31.814 --> 21:33.924
Where have you been?

21:33.975 --> 21:35.976
Out, obviously.

21:37.297 --> 21:39.297
I've been waiting for you.

21:42.739 --> 21:44.740
After you.

